# Exercise 003 - Create a PVC and see details of bounded PV

1) Create a NFS share on your Linux host;

2) Apply firewall rules to permit access to this share;

3) Create a new yaml to define a new PersistenVolume backed by the nfs share
   previously created;

4) As user "admin" define the PersistentVolume in OpenShift and show its
   details;

5) Create a new yaml to define a new PersistentVolumeClaim backed by the
   PersistentVolume previously created;

6) As user "developer" create the project "nfs-volume-test" and define the
   PersistentVolumeClaim in OpenShift;
   
7) Show if it was bounded to the correct Volume and it's details;
